Class WrapperResultSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.opitzconsulting.orcas.sql.WrapperPreparedStatement
      • de.opitzconsulting.orcas.sql.WrapperResultSet
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    WrapperIteratorResultSet, WrapperReturnValueFromResultSet

    public abstract class WrapperResultSet
extends WrapperPreparedStatement
    This wrapper wrapps a resultset, usually a WrapperReturnValueFromResultSet or a WrapperIteratorResultSet is easier to use.

      • useResultSet

        protected abstract void useResultSet(java.sql.ResultSet pResultSet)
                              throws java.sql.SQLException
        Is called when the ResultSet is ready-to-use. The first operation should be a pResultSet.next() during this method. The resultset may not be closed.

      • setParameter

        protected void setParameter(java.sql.PreparedStatement pPreparedStatement)
                     throws java.sql.SQLException
        Is called before the CallabelStatement is executed. It is usually used to set parameters. The CallableStatement may not be executed. The default implementaion does nothing.
